<subSubSection id="C3566542FFEEFFC430C60F61FD33F93F" pageId="17" pageNumber="212" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF336C9FFEEFFC430C60F61FD33F93F" blockId="17.[163,780,1369,1728]" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC430C60F61FEA0FA91" box="[163,270,1369,1390]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">Remarks:</emphasis>
According to the principle of priority of the ICZN (International Code of Zoological Nomenclature), this distinct genetic lineage was named 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C4D4AFFEEFFC4322E0FAEFD0BFA54" authorityName="Karameta &amp; Lymberakis &amp; Grillitsch &amp; Ilgaz &amp; Avci &amp; Kumlutaş &amp; Candan &amp; Wagner &amp; Sfenthourakis &amp; Pafilis &amp; Poulakakis" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="SONNINI &amp; LATREILLE" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[587,677,1430,1451]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Laudakia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="212" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC4322E0FAEFD0BFA54" box="[587,677,1430,1451]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as that is the oldest available name. It includes the morphological subspecies of 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC431530FECFE31FA16" box="[310,415,1492,1513]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">
L. s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C4D4AFFEEFFC431020FECFE31FA16" baseAuthorityName="Parker" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[359,415,1492,1513]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Laudakia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="212" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="picea">picea</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC431CF0FECFDDBFA16" box="[426,629,1492,1513]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">L. s. brachydactyla</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C4D4AFFEEFFC432E50FECFCA5FA16" baseAuthorityName="Sonnini &amp; Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[640,779,1492,1513]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Agama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="212" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="stellio" subSpecies="vulgaris">
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC432E50FECFCA5FA16" box="[640,779,1492,1513]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">L. s. vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B938EADBFFEEFFC430B10FCBFEE7F9F8" box="[212,329,1522,1544]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">L. s. salehi</emphasis>
, as well as a new phylogenetic subclade that corresponds to the 
<collectingCountry id="F35B7659FFEEFFC431D80C29FDA0F9D8" box="[445,526,1553,1575]" name="Jordan" pageId="17" pageNumber="212">Jordan</collectingCountry>
